title: Split a String Into the Max Number of Unique Substrings
content:
Given a string  return the maximum number of unique substrings that the given string can be split into.
You can split string  into any list of non-empty substrings, where the concatenation of the substrings forms the original string. However, you must split the substrings such that all of them are unique.
A substring is a contiguous sequence of characters within a string.
 






 






 contains only lower case English letters.
